
[1]treatise

   TRE'ATISE, n. [L. tractatus.] A tract; a written composition on a
   particular subject, in which the principles of it are discussed or
   explained. A treatise is of an indefinite length; but it implies more
   form and method than an essay, and less fullness or copiousness than a
   system.
